        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer237839931" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer698240476840157949">Rating: 4.125* of five<br/><br/>Witty, irreverent, and completely charming, Bennett&apos;s novella is one I would sincerely hope that Her Majesty read and laughed at when it was published.<br/><br/>There are many reviews of this effervescent entertainment, so I will confine myself to noting that the book carries with it a none-too-subtle punch line which I can&apos;t imagine would have made Mr. Bennett more likely to be in line for a life peerage, but which I can imagine made him a popular figure around Highgrove.<br/><br/>A delightfu</span>
  <span id="freeText698240476840157949" style="display:none">Rating: 4.125* of five<br><br>Witty, irreverent, and completely charming, Bennett's novella is one I would sincerely hope that Her Majesty read and laughed at when it was published.<br><br>There are many reviews of this effervescent entertainment, so I will confine myself to noting that the book carries with it a none-too-subtle punch line which I can't imagine would have made Mr. Bennett more likely to be in line for a life peerage, but which I can imagine made him a popular figure around Highgrove.<br><br>A delightful bagatelle of a book. Recommended to anyone not connected with the Royal Family. <br><br><a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/deed.en_US" rel="nofollow noopener">
